parameters:
\OC[30]\N<Phils>The adventurer's guild is located
\C[17] southeast from here. I will also listen to
the stories from those who visit the church.

\OC[30]\N<Phils>For me and everyone at the
monastery, it seems that we haven't been affected
much by 'Nightmare Heaven' so far. This is also
thanks to the blessings of the Holy Demon.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>How is that adventurer we
encountered in the dungeon doing?

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>They have calmed down quite
a bit. Although they are still staying in a
private room, there shouldn't be any issues with
having everyday conversations.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>However, it seems like they
don't remember much about what happened in the
dungeon, so it's unlikely that we'll be able to
gather much information...

\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see. However, we have found
someone who can investigate about 'Nightmare
Heaven', so there shouldn't be any issues.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>So, let's have him focus on healing
his body.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>Yes, that's right. I can't
dispel the curse right now, but I will diligently
find a way to deal with it and show you.
\OC[31]\N<Rain>Well then, I'll take my leave now.

\OC[30]\N<Phils>Yes, take care. May the blessings
of the Holy Demon be with you.

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Phils-san...? \.Are
you spacing out? Are you okay...?

\CE[94]\CE[96]\OC[30]\N<Phils>Ah, s-sorry...!
I-I'm fine...! I was just lost in thought...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see... If it's okay with
me, please feel free to consult with me if
anything happens.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Phils-san, I came to check
on you. \. How is that adventurer doing?

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>Yes, umm... \. well, I
think they're doing fine and starting to calm down
a bit.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Although it's not very
clear... Was there any problem or something?

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>N-No... umm... that kind of
thing.... It's just that, \. using up my
energy for 'treatment', so I might be a little
tired...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see... So, \. Phils-san is
the only one receiving a level of protection that
can rival 'Nightmare Heaven' at the monastery...
It must be putting a lot of strain on you.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Please wait a little longer
as I find the magic device as soon as possible...!
\. Well then, excuse me!

\OC[30]\N<Phils>(I, I can't say it... that
we're doing... \. naughty things and helping each
other reach climax...)

\OC[30]\N<Phils>(But, he said that doing that has
helped him calm down quite a bit..........\.Since
we've come this far, I can't just stop now.......

\OC[30]\N<Phils>(If I can rival the power of
Nightmare Heaven with the help of \.protection and
assistance... then, I have to do my best too...\.I
can't just rely on Rain-san completely...)

\CE[79]\CE[84]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see... Even
with the power of Phils-san's blessing...

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>Yes... It seems
difficult to completely prevent 'Nightmare
Heaven'...

\OC[30]\N<Phils>That magic seems to constantly
circulate through space like air, so even if we
temporarily negate its effects, it will only
amplify desires again over time...

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>By the way... I think
places and people protected by the divine
blessings of \. are relatively safe, but how are
we dealing with those who are not protected?

\CE[79]\CE[78]\CE[83]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Those
whose desires have been amplified often seek
money... or they frequently come seeking physical
intimacy...

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>It seems that most
people easily amplify their sexual desires... \.
So, for those individuals... we try to respond to
their desires as much as possible...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Rather than causing harm
to ordinary people, and...

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>And... I've also been
affected by the effects of 'Nightmare Heaven' to
some extent... S-So, in other words, there are
times when it gets resolved for me too...

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I-I'm sorry for
surprising you... B-But, this is the only solution
we can currently come up with...

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>Y-Yes, that's right...! \.
No, sacrificing myself to protect the people of
the town from the clutches of evil.........!

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Please keep this
a secret from Caldo-san and Fristo-san...

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>Yes..........\. But......
please take good care of your body.......\. If you
need any treatment, please let me know
anytime.......

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Hey, Phils... Your
face is all red, isn't it?

\CE[94]\CE[96]\OC[30]\N<Phils>Eh... Is that so?
Well, there's nothing wrong with me...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Is that so... considering
the situation, please take a rest without pushing
yourself.

\N<Phils>Rain-san... um, I'm having trouble with
where to look... so if you could wear clothing
with a little less exposure, I would appreciate
it...

\EMP Huh... why is there someone dressed so
provocatively here... m-maybe they're just
tired...

\EMP Lately, my concentration has been easily
disrupted... Focus, focus...!

\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>For now, I had them
enter a private room... but is it really okay to
protect them here?

\OC[31]\N<Rain>Even though it's because of magic,
he is still in danger like this. Shouldn't we have
him enter the prison cell in the guard station...?

\CE[94]\CE[79]\OC[30]\N<Phils>I see... but that
person is the victim, so it would be pitiful to
put them in a prison cell...

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>Besides, there are other
monks here, so I'm sure it'll be fine!

\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>... I understand.
However, please let me know immediately if you
need any help.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>Rain-san, what are you
going to do from now on?

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>For now, I understand that
'Nightmare Heaven' cannot be dispelled by the
usual method.

\CE[78]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>If even the experts
in healing and dispelling curses from the church
can't undo it, honestly, right now we have no
choice but to accept it...

\CE[78]\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>But, Phils-
san's treatment has slightly alleviated his
symptoms. And the fact that he can resist with
magic and mental strength like me means that there
must be a solution.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>In order to find that, I will try
to find someone who can analyze this magic using
the fragments of the device I picked up in the
dungeon as a clue.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>I see...! If we can analyze
it, we might be able to find a way to dispel the
curse!

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Do you have any idea
of a place in this town where magicians gather?

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>In that case, in
this town there is a Adventurer's Guild located
southeast from here, so there might be magicians
there.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>I'm sorry for becoming a
burden... I don't seem to be of much help right
now...

\CE[79]\CE[84]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>No, I haven't
been able to do anything yet. \. Phils-san, I'm
counting on you to take care of him on the second
floor.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>Understood. \. May the
blessings of the Holy Demon be with us.

\CE[79]\CE[78]\CE[84]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner
Rain>(That eerie aura... It was present when it
attacked me in the dungeon too... That's probably
the very desire that overflowed from Nightmare
Heaven...!)

\CE[78]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(If things
continue like this... according to Demon's words,
does that mean all the residents of this town will
end up in a state like him...?)

\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(Until we find a
solution, we have to somehow satisfy \C[17]desires
and help them regain some rationality\C[13]...!)
All the events in town have been unlocked.

\N<Frist>...I see, the clear crystal was stolen by
the thief...

\N<Frist>However, I'm glad that Sister Phils and
Rain-san have both returned safely. First, let's
rejoice in that fact.

\N<Frist>However, Sister Phils, you're being too
reckless. Even considering the circumstances,
going alone like that...

\N<Phils>I'm sorry... but if we continue like
this...

\N<Rain>Let's ask the guards to search for the
clear crystal. It may not be found immediately,
but I think it's better than doing nothing...

\N<Frist>I see... However, we still need to hurry
and find a fundamental solution...

\N<Rain>Yes... Since the thief was always one step
ahead of me and Phils, there's a high possibility
that we're being watched. If we act recklessly,
we'll just end up getting in the way again...

\N<Rain>I think I know the location of the third
device soon, so I'll go there. But please be
careful here and at the church as well.

\N<Phils>I was able to make one with the clear
crystal we retrieved. I think it's better if Rain-
san has it.

\N<Phils>It should be able to prevent some 'Desire
Manipulation Techniques', and although it's only
once, if you break it, a temporarily powerful
protective force will be activated!

\N<Rain>Thank you very much. This will be our
trump card.

\N<Phils>I hate to say this... but Rain-san,
please be careful not to push yourself too hard!
